post_text:
A “Reverse Parade” will be held on Monday, June 15th . It will be rain or shine. It will be held at East Meadow parking lot (between GJSHS and EM) from 11:00 am to 1:00 pm (PreK, K, & 1st 11-11:30, 2nd & 3rd 11:30-12, 4th & 5th 12-12:30 & 6th from 12:30-1).
A Reverse Parade means that the EM staff will be lined up along the perimeters of the EM and GJSHS parking lots (along the bus route, between the schools, and in front of GJSHS). Students and families will be able to “drive-through” the parade in their cars. Please do not stop as you drive through.
Please see the information and guidelines at https://5il.co/h5gr
We hope to see you there!
text:

A Reverse Parade means that the EM staff will be lined up along the perimeters of the EM and GJSHS parking lots (along the bus route, between the schools, and in front of GJSHS). Students and families will be able to “drive-through” the parade in their cars. Please do not stop as you drive through.

East Meadow Cares Parade

East Meadow Cares Parade

post_text:
Several of the staff from East Meadow have organized a parade through Granby this Thursday to show their dedication and support to our families. The parade will begin from West Street at 1:00 P.M. The route will be posted on Good News Granby (Facebook), the district web page and APP, as well as below.
They ask that you please follow the guidelines below for everyone's safety.
~All people should stay safely away from the vehicles.
~We need to practice social distancing, so teachers will not be getting out of cars to say hello.
~We are unable to drive down each street in town. please remember that if you walk to the top of the streets to see the parade, keep a safe distance from others.
~We are going to send out 3-4 cars, every two minutes, to stagger the traffic.

post_text: Great to see our 5th and 6th-grade students from East Meadow actively participating in the Granby Jr/Sr High School Health Fair thanks to Nurse Leader, Nancy Jenks. Many of the stations were developed and manned by their high school peers. There is an abundance of local community partners sharing information. The students are learning about healthy food & nutrition, asthma, health conditions, body functions, road safety, stress management, learning how to care for emergency bleeding, substance abuse and prevention, mental health, skincare and protection, injury prevention, and age-appropriate sexual and reproductive health.

post_text:
Update Athletics Announcement: GJSHS is closed today. There will be no basketball tryouts today 12.4.19). Both crews are working hard to resolve the issue. With the uncertainly of how long it will take to resolve the issue and our concern about parents being able to make arrangements for their children to make it back to school, we ultimately feel it's better to remain cancelled.

I have been in contact with all coaches to coordinate additional times for tryouts. I will send a schedule out later today outlining practice times. Our hope is to resume tomorrow as scheduled.

Thank you for your continued patience. If you have any questions, please email ajordan-gagner@granbyschoolsma.net

post_text: Due to the water pipe burst, GJSHS is cancelled for today 12/4. This is a regular cancellation and no Blizzard Bag will be used for today. Thank you for your patience as we work to resolve this issue as quickly as possible.
text: Due to the water pipe burst, GJSHS is cancelled for today 12/4. This is a regular cancellation and no Blizzard Bag will be used for today. Thank you for your patience as we work to resolve this issue as quickly as possible.

post_text:
We are monitoring a water pipe that has burst in the GJSHS cafeteria near the exterior door where students enter the building in the morning. We will continue to monitor the situation overnight. Repair work has been scheduled for tomorrow morning.

At this point, GJSHS ONLY will have a two hour delay. Elementary students will be picked up at their normal times for a regular start of school. The busses will then pick up GJSHS high school students.

Should the situation change at GJSHS, we will use the normal channels to communicate with our families in the morning.

Thank you to our facilities and custodial staff who will monitor the situation overnight and work to get repairs made as quickly as possible. The entire team has jumped to do whatever they can to help.

Thank you, and have a wonderful evening.
